Author, writing teacher and frequent Tampa Bay Times contributor Roy Peter Clark will present a writing workshop and talk about his upcoming book, “Tell It Like It Is: A Guide to Clear and Honest Writing,” at 3:30 p.m. Jan. 22 at the Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Admission $5; oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Tombolo Books commemorates International Holocaust Remembrance Day with authors Barbara Weigen Bergren (”Witness for My Father”) and Ruth Finkel Wade (”The Ones Who Remember”) discussing and signing their books at 7 p.m. Jan. 26 at the bookstore, 2153 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Free; RSVP at tombolobooks.com/events. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.